# Event context

This project is **LeaseLens AI** for the **Abu Dhabi AI PropTech Challenge**
("Building the Intelligence Layer for Land, Investment and Communities") — a
one-day event at Hub71. Optimize for **demo-by-tonight**, not production.

## Track

**Future Communities (Track 3)** — AI lease operations that keep Abu Dhabi
residential communities compliant and occupancy-stable.

## What this codebase is

- Next.js 14 (App Router) + TypeScript + Tailwind + shadcn/ui bento dashboard.
- `src/components/dashboard/upload-zone.tsx` — drag-drop PDF → 3s mock "AI extracting clauses..."
- `src/components/dashboard/extracted-data-panel.tsx` — shows parsed lease fields after upload.
- `src/components/dashboard/renewal-notice-dialog.tsx` — WhatsApp/email renewal drafts.
- `scripts/build-lease-data.mjs` — preprocesses starter-kit CSVs into `src/data/lease-portfolio.json`.
- Real model calls belong in a route handler so keys stay server-side; keys in `.env.local` only.

## Event data

- Synthetic datasets from starter-kit, joined on `district`:
  `sample_listings`, `sample_communities`, `districts`.
- Source: https://github.com/abu-dhabi-ai-proptech-challenge/starter-kit/tree/main/data
- Ejari/expiry/tenant fields are **synthetic demo extensions** on listing rows — not in the CSV.
- Never present synthetic values as real Abu Dhabi market data.

## How to help this team win

- Bias toward the **single demo path working end to end**; cut scope before adding features.
- Keep components small and obvious.
- Judging rewards: sharp problem framing, working prototype, AI doing real work,
  demo readiness, and credible impact.
